s to formulate his response, and also look at another brief autobiographical text by Einstein, written a few weeks before his death, which is published here for the first time in English.Complete with evocative drawings by artist Laurent Taudin, Einstein on Einstein illuminates the iconic physicist's journey to general relativity while situating his revolutionary ideas alongside other astonishing scientific breakthroughs of the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aPhysicistsvBiography. 0aPhysicistsxIntellectual life. 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh  aAnnus Mirabilis.  aBrownian motion.  aCharles Darwin.  aE=MC2.  aEinstein's brain.  aGalileo Galilei.  aIdeas and Opinions.  aIsaac Newton.  aMarie Curie.  aMax Planck.  aNeils Bohr.  aNikola Tesla.  aOut of My Later Years.  aPaul Arthur Schilpp.  aSir Arthur Eddington.  aStephen Hawking.  aThe Meaning of Relativity.  aThe World as I See It.  aThomas Edison.  aWalter Isaacson.  ablack holes.  agravitational lensing.  agravitational waves.  aphotoelectric effect.  aquantum theory.  aspace-time.  aspecial relativity.  aspeed of light.  atheory of gravity.  atheory of relativity.  aunified field theory.1 aGutfreund, Hanoch, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069008840uhttps://doi.org/10